This repository contains draft material for an in-progress PhD dissertation.
Three tiers of material are distinguished:

1. PROSE + FIGURES (`.qmd` files, `figures/`, `drafts/`, generated `_book/`
   output): All rights reserved until the relevant chapter is accepted for
   publication. You may view, but not redistribute, adapt, or use in derivative
   works without written permission from the author.

2. BIBLIOGRAPHY DATA (`.bib` files): Metadata pulled from public DOIs.
   Free to reuse.

3. ANALYSIS CODE (everything under `code/`): Dual-licensed.
   (a) Until the chapter that uses the code is published: academic use only,
       with attribution. Not for commercial redistribution.
   (b) After the first publication that uses the code: released under the MIT
       License (text below), retroactively applying to the code as of the
       publication date.

